From: TONY JOHN, Port Harcourt In a brazen attack weekend, some gunmen stormed the home of an official of the Kalabari Kingdom and abducted his wife.
Identified as Mrs. S. Damiete, the woman is the Principal of Kalabari National College (KNC), Buguma, headquarters of Asari-Toru Local Government Area of Rivers State.
Witnesses said the Principal was kidnapped on Saturday, at about 7:30pm by unknown gunmen
As at the time of filing the report, information about her abduction was sketchy.
The State Police Public Relations Officer, Omoni Nnamdi, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), could not confirm the report at press time, as a text message sent to him about the incident, was not replied. 